00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:06,619
it's been preserved, providentially preserved.

229
00:15:06,619 --> 00:15:09,739
It was given by inspiration, but it's preserved for us.

230
00:15:09,739 --> 00:15:15,100
And we can know what God wants us to know as we study this book.

231
00:15:15,739 --> 00:15:17,500
And we have people today that are running around.

232
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:18,540
They want to have a vision.

233
00:15:18,540 --> 00:15:21,820
They want to have a revelation, but they don't want to look at this book.

234
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:26,779
They then take, perhaps they would look at their vision or their revelation

235
00:15:26,779 --> 00:15:31,179
and they would put it as being superior to God's word.

236
00:15:32,540 --> 00:15:33,260
It's a problem.

237
00:15:34,139 --> 00:15:36,380
The apostle Paul, he was given visions.

238
00:15:36,380 --> 00:15:39,500
Now, let me say this about visions and revelations.

239
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:42,059
And we understand that Paul is speaking the truth here

240
00:15:42,059 --> 00:15:43,899
and he's giving the truth, but he says,

241
00:15:43,899 --> 00:15:45,820
I can't speak about these things.

242
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:49,019
And he then begins to talk about glorying in the Lord.

243
00:15:49,019 --> 00:15:52,700
But someone like Paul that had visions or revelations,

244
00:15:52,700 --> 00:15:55,739
if he handled it the way that the Judaizers did,

245
00:15:55,739 --> 00:15:56,940
oh, that would puff him up.

246
00:15:57,579 --> 00:15:59,179
That caused him to be prideful.

247
00:15:59,179 --> 00:16:05,820
That would cause him to boast in the fact that God chose me to give me

248
00:16:05,820 --> 00:16:09,179
and we find that it could lead to pride.

249
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,139
God knows our frame.

250
00:16:12,139 --> 00:16:13,179
Aren't you thankful for that?

251
00:16:13,899 --> 00:16:15,019
He knows your heart.

252
00:16:15,019 --> 00:16:17,260
You know, the Bible tells us that the heart is deceitful

253
00:16:17,260 --> 00:16:20,700
and it's desperately wicked in Jeremiah 17.

254
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:23,899
And then the question is this, who can know it?

255
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:28,700
I, the Lord, try the rains.

256
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:29,820
He tries the heart.

257
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:31,260
He knows your heart.

258
00:16:31,260 --> 00:16:32,299
You read through the scriptures.

259
00:16:32,299 --> 00:16:35,500
You find that the Bible says that God, he knew their thoughts.

260
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:36,459
Isn't that amazing?

261
00:16:37,179 --> 00:16:38,139
God knows us.

262
00:16:38,139 --> 00:16:39,339
He knows our hearts.

263
00:16:39,339 --> 00:16:42,700
He knows that we are, he knows our frame.

264
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:47,260
He knows that we're prone to wander, that we're prone to being prideful.

265
00:16:47,260 --> 00:16:49,260
And we find that in the text of scripture

266
00:16:49,260 --> 00:16:52,700
that Paul speaks about these revelations, these visions.

267
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:55,179
And so Paul was given a vision,

268
00:16:55,179 --> 00:16:57,660
but we find that Paul was not only given a vision,

269
00:16:57,660 --> 00:16:59,419
but number two, he was given a thorn.

270
00:17:01,660 --> 00:17:02,940
He was given a thorn.

271
00:17:02,940 --> 00:17:05,660
I want you to think about this in comparison this morning.

272
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:12,139
If you were to be the recipient of a vision of having revelation,

273
00:17:12,139 --> 00:17:13,899
that might cause you to be prideful.

274
00:17:13,899 --> 00:17:17,339
It might cause you to think highly of yourself.

275
00:17:17,339 --> 00:17:19,739
It may cause you to rejoice and to be thankful

276
00:17:19,739 --> 00:17:22,459
that you had this vision or this revelation,

277
00:17:23,739 --> 00:17:26,459
but a thorn, a thorn.

278
00:17:27,739 --> 00:17:31,100
See, oftentimes we take the same approach that the apostle Paul does

279
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:34,139
in beseeching the Lord to remove the thorn.

280
00:17:34,139 --> 00:17:35,980
And we'll get to that in just a few moments.

281
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:40,540
But I want you to focus just for a moment here this morning

282
00:17:40,540 --> 00:17:44,459
on this truth that Paul was given a thorn.

283
00:17:45,339 --> 00:17:46,059
We think about this.

284
00:17:46,059 --> 00:17:47,899
Notice what the Bible says in verse number six.

285
00:17:47,899 --> 00:17:51,100
For though I would desire to glory, I shall not be a fool,

286
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:52,220
for I will say the truth.

287
00:17:52,940 --> 00:17:55,980
But now I forbear, lest any man should think of me above that

288
00:17:56,619 --> 00:18:01,019
which he seemeth me to be, or that he heareth of me.

289
00:18:01,019 --> 00:18:04,459
And lest I should be exalted above measure,

290
00:18:04,459 --> 00:18:06,700
through the abundance of the revelation,

291
00:18:06,700 --> 00:18:12,139
there was given to me a thorn in the flesh.

292
00:18:13,820 --> 00:18:17,260
There was given to me a thorn in the flesh.

293
00:18:17,260 --> 00:18:18,139
Who gave it to him?

294
00:18:19,980 --> 00:18:20,299
God.

295
00:18:22,139 --> 00:18:23,339
Who gave him the visions?

296
00:18:23,980 --> 00:18:25,339
Who gave him the revelations?

297
00:18:26,220 --> 00:18:26,540
God.

298
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:28,859
But then God gave him a thorn.

299
00:18:30,940 --> 00:18:36,299
Sometimes our perspective in life is not really biblical.

300
00:18:36,859 --> 00:18:38,299
What do I mean by that?

301
00:18:38,299 --> 00:18:44,219
Sometimes when we see this pleasant thing, this good thing,

302
00:18:44,219 --> 00:18:46,700
we say, oh, God gave me this.

303
00:18:48,779 --> 00:18:51,419
But then we see something that from our perspective,

304
00:18:51,419 --> 00:18:54,219
from our vantage point is not that pleasant thing

305
00:18:54,219 --> 00:18:57,340
or that good thing and we are disappointed in it.

306
00:18:57,979 --> 00:19:03,099
We don't rejoice for the thorn like we rejoice for the visions.

307
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:05,820
But I want you to understand this morning

308
00:19:05,820 --> 00:19:11,260
that the thorn came from God and the thorn was necessary.

309
00:19:11,260 --> 00:19:14,380
And the thorn is reason to rejoice.

310
00:19:14,380 --> 00:19:14,779
Why?

311
00:19:14,779 --> 00:19:18,940
Because the Bible says twice in our passage of Scripture,

312
00:19:18,940 --> 00:19:22,700
lest I should be exalted above measure.

313
00:19:22,779 --> 00:19:25,099
What happens when we get full of pride?

314
00:19:26,940 --> 00:19:27,979
Destroys us.

315
00:19:27,979 --> 00:19:29,820
Can I remind you of what the Bible says?

316
00:19:29,820 --> 00:19:34,219
The Bible says this, God resisteth the what?

317
00:19:35,179 --> 00:19:35,739
The proud.

318
00:19:37,580 --> 00:19:41,020
So Paul says there was given to me a thorn in the flesh.

319
00:19:41,020 --> 00:19:41,820
Why?

320
00:19:41,820 --> 00:19:45,820
Lest I should be exalted above measure.

321
00:19:45,820 --> 00:19:51,659
And if I'm exalted above measure, if I am full of pride, God resists me.

322
00:19:53,419 --> 00:19:54,460
Am I telling you the truth?

323
00:19:56,299 --> 00:19:59,900
God hates pride.

324
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:02,640
God hates pride.

325
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:05,620
God resisteth the proud,

326
00:20:05,620 --> 00:20:07,580
and what's the rest of the verse?

327
00:20:07,580 --> 00:20:11,500
But giveth grace unto the humble.

328
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:12,940
Amen?

329
00:20:12,940 --> 00:20:15,640
And we find that as we study the Word of God

330
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:18,020
and we look at this passage of Scripture,

331
00:20:18,020 --> 00:20:19,860
we find that the Apostle Paul,

332
00:20:19,860 --> 00:20:21,940
he's speaking to the believers in Corinth,

333
00:20:21,940 --> 00:20:23,620
and he says there was given to me

334
00:20:23,620 --> 00:20:25,620
visions and revelations,

335
00:20:25,620 --> 00:20:30,060
but there was given a thorn.

336
00:20:30,060 --> 00:20:31,260
A thorn.

337
00:20:31,260 --> 00:20:33,660
Many have debated what this thorn is.

338
00:20:33,660 --> 00:20:35,940
Many have had their ideas

339
00:20:35,940 --> 00:20:38,220
and they've set forth their reasons

340
00:20:38,220 --> 00:20:40,460
of why they believe what they believe

341
00:20:40,460 --> 00:20:41,900
with regard to the thorn.

342
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:43,740
We find that Paul simply says

343
00:20:43,740 --> 00:20:46,780
there was given to me a thorn in the flesh.

344
00:20:46,780 --> 00:20:49,540
The messenger of Satan to buffet me

345
00:20:49,540 --> 00:20:53,700
lest I should be exalted above measure.

346
00:20:53,700 --> 00:20:55,980
Isn't it interesting in verse 7

347
00:20:55,980 --> 00:20:59,380
that bookends to the verse of Scripture

348
00:20:59,380 --> 00:21:04,620
are lest I should be exalted above measure.

349
00:21:04,620 --> 00:21:08,620
Do you think God wants us to stay humble?

350
00:21:08,620 --> 00:21:09,780
Absolutely.

351
00:21:09,780 --> 00:21:12,260
Did Nebuchadnezzar find that God

352
00:21:12,260 --> 00:21:15,100
could humble a man?

353
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:17,820
He found out the hard way, did he not?

354
00:21:17,820 --> 00:21:20,020
And at the end of the whole situation,

355
00:21:20,020 --> 00:21:21,540
did Nebuchadnezzar recognize

356
00:21:21,540 --> 00:21:25,020
that God is able to humble?

357
00:21:25,020 --> 00:21:26,980
But you know what Peter tells us?

358
00:21:26,980 --> 00:21:31,260
Humble yourselves in the sight of God.

359
00:21:31,260 --> 00:21:34,620
Humble yourselves in the sight of God.

360
00:21:34,620 --> 00:21:36,380
And there are some things that God

361
00:21:36,380 --> 00:21:38,620
will bring into your life and into my life

362
00:21:38,620 --> 00:21:40,180
to keep us humble.

363
00:21:40,180 --> 00:21:42,860
Just like God did here for the Apostle Paul,

364
00:21:42,860 --> 00:21:45,780
and the Bible says that He gave him a thorn,

365
00:21:45,780 --> 00:21:48,700
this experience of these visions and revelations

366
00:21:48,740 --> 00:21:51,180
could lead to pride, could lead to glory,

367
00:21:51,180 --> 00:21:54,060
but we find God in His infinite wisdom,

368
00:21:54,060 --> 00:21:57,620
He gave to Paul this thorn in the flesh.

369
00:21:58,740 --> 00:22:02,260
And Paul besought the Lord that this thing would depart

370
00:22:02,260 --> 00:22:05,220
and God in a single word said no,

371
00:22:05,220 --> 00:22:07,620
we'll look at the entirety of it in just a moment,

372
00:22:07,620 --> 00:22:12,380
but we find that God knows best.

373
00:22:12,380 --> 00:22:14,100
God knows what you need.

374
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:15,700
He knows what I need.

375
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:18,100
He knows what will happen in our lives

376
00:22:18,100 --> 00:22:19,620
given certain circumstances

377
00:22:19,620 --> 00:22:24,620
and how we might be led to not trust Him like we should.

378
00:22:26,180 --> 00:22:27,900
That we'll come to a place where we begin

379
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:32,260
to lean on our own understanding like we should not.

380
00:22:32,260 --> 00:22:33,740
Right, you understand what I'm saying?

381
00:22:33,740 --> 00:22:36,740
And God will allow things in our lives.

382
00:22:36,740 --> 00:22:40,060
God will allow things to cause us to come to a place,

383
00:22:40,060 --> 00:22:43,300
listen, to depend on Him.

384
00:22:44,300 --> 00:22:45,140
Have you ever been in a place

385
00:22:45,140 --> 00:22:46,820
where you just didn't know what to do?

386
00:22:48,140 --> 00:22:50,780
I was having discipleship and training

387
00:22:50,780 --> 00:22:53,580
with Fernando last week and he asked me a question.

388
00:22:53,580 --> 00:22:55,340
He said, have you ever felt like it's hard?

389
00:22:55,340 --> 00:22:56,180
Have you ever felt like you don't know what to do?

390
00:22:56,180 --> 00:22:59,700
And I said, Fernando, listen, let me just tell you,

391
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:02,180
there's plenty of times that you see it's hard

392
00:23:02,180 --> 00:23:04,100
and you don't know what to do

393
00:23:04,100 --> 00:23:06,620
and it's not just at the beginning,

394
00:23:06,620 --> 00:23:08,940
it's throughout the life and ministry

395
00:23:08,940 --> 00:23:11,420
of a follower of the Lord Jesus Christ.

396
00:23:11,420 --> 00:23:14,060
And we find that what is God doing in those moments?

397
00:23:14,060 --> 00:23:16,500
He's leading us to a place of dependence,

398
00:23:17,340 --> 00:23:21,580
depending upon Him, seeking Him for direction,

399
00:23:21,580 --> 00:23:25,420
seeking Him for what is next.

400
00:23:25,420 --> 00:23:28,580
And we find that as you study through the Psalms

401
00:23:28,580 --> 00:23:30,780
and we have on Wednesday nights here,

402
00:23:30,780 --> 00:23:33,900
the last several weeks that David was in a place

403
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:36,700
where he needed direction and he sought the Lord.

404
00:23:36,700 --> 00:23:38,500
There were some circumstances in his life

405
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:41,240
that brought him to that place of dependence.

406
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:44,420
We see that the purpose is given to us

407
00:23:44,420 --> 00:23:46,780
in verse number seven as bookends to the verse

408
00:23:46,780 --> 00:23:49,380
that lest I should be exalted above measure.

409
00:23:49,380 --> 00:23:52,420
But I want you to understand that as we look at this thorn

410
00:23:52,420 --> 00:23:56,900
that Paul received, that this result of this thorn

411
00:23:56,900 --> 00:24:00,380
would bring humility and dependence.

412
00:24:00,380 --> 00:24:04,220
Can I tell you this morning that we need both?

413
00:24:05,540 --> 00:24:06,580
We need both.

414
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:08,820
We need to be humble.

415
00:24:11,020 --> 00:24:12,900
We need to be dependent upon the Lord.

416
00:24:13,780 --> 00:24:15,660
Sometimes what happens, Brother Mike and I

417
00:24:15,660 --> 00:24:18,780
were talking last night, and as we were talking

418
00:24:18,780 --> 00:24:21,740
after we had dinner and the kids were playing

419
00:24:21,740 --> 00:24:24,660
and his son wanted to beat everybody at UNO

420
00:24:24,660 --> 00:24:26,940
and we were just kind of talking for a few minutes

421
00:24:26,940 --> 00:24:30,380
before we got into the UNO game and we began to talk

422
00:24:30,380 --> 00:24:32,940
about preparing messages and that sort of thing.

423
00:24:32,940 --> 00:24:35,660
And I said this to him.

424
00:24:35,660 --> 00:24:39,560
I said, you know, the message is important,

425
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:44,180
but the man is of greater importance, the vessel.

426
00:24:45,320 --> 00:24:46,160
The vessel.

427
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:50,600
And sometimes what can happen is we can get so professional

428
00:24:51,840 --> 00:24:54,720
and so methodical in the Christian life

429
00:24:56,180 --> 00:24:57,680
that we just figure out how to do it

430
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:59,360
like it's a well-oiled machine.

431
00:25:00,280 --> 00:25:01,740
But that's not ministry.

432
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:05,160
Ministry is to be lived in dependence.

433
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:07,780
Your Christian life is to be lived in dependence

434
00:25:07,780 --> 00:25:11,060
every single day on the Lord Jesus Christ.

435
00:25:11,060 --> 00:25:14,560
Because when he said in John 15 that ye are the branches

436
00:25:14,560 --> 00:25:17,860
and I am the vine, and without me you can do nothing,

437
00:25:17,860 --> 00:25:20,620
he was speaking truth that was necessary

438
00:25:20,620 --> 00:25:23,700
for his people to understand and to accept.

439
00:25:24,660 --> 00:25:27,700
There are times in which we get so focused.

440
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:30,420
I preached last Sunday night of too busy for Jesus

441
00:25:30,420 --> 00:25:33,060
and looking at Martha and that whole situation

442
00:25:33,060 --> 00:25:36,020
and we can just get so busy serving the master

443
00:25:36,060 --> 00:25:38,860
that we forget to spend time with the master.

444
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:41,860
Ministry is important, serving is important,

445
00:25:41,860 --> 00:25:44,940
but we cannot forego, we cannot forfeit

446
00:25:44,940 --> 00:25:47,380
our time with Christ.

447
00:25:47,380 --> 00:25:51,140
So Paul was given visions, Paul was given a thorn.

448
00:25:51,140 --> 00:25:53,460
And let me say this as we finish up this morning,

449
00:25:53,460 --> 00:25:55,680
number three, Paul was given an answer.

450
00:25:56,780 --> 00:25:58,500
Paul was given an answer.

451
00:25:58,500 --> 00:25:59,940
As we look at verses eight and nine,

452
00:25:59,940 --> 00:26:04,100
the Bible records for us this request that Paul makes

453
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:05,580
and the answer that he receives.

454
00:26:06,180 --> 00:26:07,060
The request is simple.

455
00:26:07,060 --> 00:26:09,180
In verse number eight, for this thing,

456
00:26:09,180 --> 00:26:13,980
I besought the Lord thrice that it might depart from me.

457
00:26:13,980 --> 00:26:16,220
It's very plain what Paul was requesting.

458
00:26:16,220 --> 00:26:19,420
In fact, for some of us, we've prayed the same type

459
00:26:19,420 --> 00:26:21,580
of prayer that Paul has prayed.

460
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:25,260
We pray in a situation, God, would you remove this?

461
00:26:25,260 --> 00:26:26,380
Why do we pray that way?

462
00:26:26,380 --> 00:26:28,100
Because we believe that he can.

463
00:26:30,660 --> 00:26:32,860
I believe that God can move the mountains.

464
00:26:32,860 --> 00:26:34,920
I believe that God can part the seas.

465
00:26:35,280 --> 00:26:37,360
I believe that God is still on his throne.

466
00:26:37,360 --> 00:26:39,800
He has all the power that he's ever had

467
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:41,040
and that he ever will have.

468
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:42,360
He is omnipotent.

469
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:45,880
He is able to do exceeding abundantly above

470
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:47,720
all that we ask or think.

471
00:26:48,780 --> 00:26:52,080
And I pray at times that God would remove something.

472
00:26:52,080 --> 00:26:52,920
Why?

473
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:55,140
Because I believe that he can.

474
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:58,360
And Paul besought the Lord thrice.

475
00:26:58,360 --> 00:27:02,120
This was not something that just one time he prayed.

476
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:03,400
No, it was three times.

477
00:27:03,400 --> 00:27:06,520
There's an element, an aspect of maybe fervency

478
00:27:06,520 --> 00:27:09,700
that we could speak of here with regard to the request.

479
00:27:09,700 --> 00:27:12,000
And Paul sought the Lord.

480
00:27:13,520 --> 00:27:15,580
He knew that God was able.

481
00:27:15,580 --> 00:27:17,960
But we find that Paul was given an answer.

482
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:20,800
Can I say it this way even before we read verse number nine?

483
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:23,600
It may not always be the answer that we're looking for.

484
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:28,080
I think Paul was looking for an answer

485
00:27:28,080 --> 00:27:30,360
that was different than the answer that he received.

486
00:27:30,360 --> 00:27:32,440
I think that Paul truly desired

487
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:36,400
that God would remove that thorn.

488
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:37,600
That's why he prayed it.

489
